# Agent Standards

## Structure
Every agent is a standalone function in src/agents/.
Signature: agent_name(state: ValidatorState) -> dict

## Output
Every agent returns a typed Pydantic v2 model.
No raw strings. No dicts. No untyped returns.

## FORBIDDEN VOCABULARY rule (non-negotiable)
Every agent prompt MUST include a block like this:

  FORBIDDEN VOCABULARY — never use these exact terms in output:
  [list every field name from the output schema here]
  Write in clear natural language only.

This prevents schema field leakage into user-facing prose.
(This failure cost 3 debugging sessions in Project 1.)

## Model routing
CHEAP_MODEL  → Job Intelligence, Rate Intelligence
STRONG_MODEL → Proposal Analyst, Win Strategy
Source from settings.cheap_model_name / settings.strong_model_name

## Error handling
Raise AgentCallError on LLM call failure.
Raise SchemaValidationError on Pydantic parse failure.
Never let raw exceptions propagate to the orchestrator.
